question: Will Gitanas Nauseda win the 2024 Lithuanian presidential election?
description:
This market concerns the 2024 Lithuanian presidential election. The first round of Lithuania's 2024 presidential election is scheduled for May 12. If no candidate receives more than half of the votes, a second round with the two candidates receiving the most votes will occur on May 26.

This market will resolve to "Yes" if Gitanas Nauseda wins the 2024 Lithuanian presidential election. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

This market includes any potential second round. If the result of this election isn't known by December 31, 2024, 11:59 PM ET, the market will resolve to "No".

In the case of a two-round election, if this candidate is eliminated before the second round, this market may immediately resolve to "No".

The primary resolution source for this market will be official information from Lithuania; however, a consensus of credible reporting will also suffice.

question: Will 'Kingdom of the Planet of the Apes' gross less than $46m on its opening weekend?
description:
This is a market on how much 'Kingdom of the Planet of the Apes' (2024) will gross domestically on its opening weekend. The “Domestic Weekend” tab on https://www.boxofficemojo.com/title/tt11389872/ will be used to resolve this market once the values for the 3-day opening weekend (May 10 - May 12) are final (i.e. not studio estimates).

This market will resolve to "Yes" if 'Kingdom of the Planet of the Apes' (2024) grosses less than $46,000,000 on its 3-day opening weekend. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

Please note, this market will resolve according to the Box Office Mojo numbers under Domestic Weekend for the 3-day weekend (which typically includes Thursday's previews), regardless of whether domestic refers to only the USA, or to USA and Canada, etc.

If there is no final data available by May 20, 2024, 11:59 PM ET, another credible resolution source will be chosen.

question: Will PTB win the most seats in the Belgian federal elections?
description:
Belgium is scheduled to hold federal elections for the Chamber of Representatives (lower house of parliament) on June 9, 2024. 

This market will resolve to "Yes" if the Workers' Party of Belgium (PTB) wins more seats than any other party in the Chamber of Representatives as a result of the 2024 Belgian federal elections. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

If voting in the 2024 Belgian federal elections do not occur by December 31, 2024, this market will resolve to "No".

In the case of a tie between this party and any other for the most seats gained, this market will resolve in favor of the party whose listed abbreviation comes first in alphabetical order.

This market's resolution will be based solely on the number of seats won by the PTB, not any coalition of which it may be a part.

The primary resolution source for this market will be official information from the Belgian government, however, a consensus of credible reporting may also be used.

events.title: Belgian Election: Which party wins the most seats?

question: RFK Jr. wins a state?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Robert F. Kennedy Jr. wins the popular vote in any state in the 2024 US presidential election. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

Only statewide popular vote results will be considered. Washington D.C., territories and individual congressional district electors will not count towards the resolution of this market.

This market may resolve immediately if at least one state has been called for Robert F. Kennedy Jr. for President by the Associated Press, Fox News, and NBC or if all states have been called by the Associated Press, Fox News, and NBC.

The resolution source for this market is the Associated Press, Fox News, and NBC. If all three sources haven’t called the race for all states for the same candidate, this market will resolve based on the official certification.
